00:47:31.190 --> 00:47:33.230
a few million dollars

00:47:33.230 --> 00:47:34.610
to set up a company to

00:47:36.140 --> 00:47:39.840
investigate this for commercial purposes

00:47:39.840 --> 00:47:42.360
and to build a reasonable system

00:47:42.360 --> 00:47:45.500
for delivering the covalent linkage

00:47:45.500 --> 00:47:47.450
of the basic peptide to the morpholino.

00:47:48.620 --> 00:47:51.330
So I don't know anybody
with a few million dollars

00:47:51.330 --> 00:47:53.030
who's willing to do that.

00:47:53.030 --> 00:47:55.680
And I'm not a great entrepreneur,

00:47:55.680 --> 00:47:57.563
so I can't do anything about it.

00:47:58.410 --> 00:47:59.243
- [Audience Member] I
have a follow-up question.

00:47:59.243 --> 00:48:02.010
Is it easier to design an EGS for viruses

00:48:03.010 --> 00:48:04.273
as opposed to cancers?

00:48:05.287 --> 00:48:06.930
- In concept and in principle, you could

00:48:06.930 --> 00:48:09.290
for a virus, certainly for viruses.

00:48:09.290 --> 00:48:11.003
And that's what Fenyong is doing.

00:48:13.320 --> 00:48:14.153
- [Audience Member] Well, I wanna follow

00:48:14.153 --> 00:48:16.010
was Stu's question.

00:48:16.010 --> 00:48:18.380
How much we know about the biogenesis

00:48:18.380 --> 00:48:21.437
of the enzyme in terms of the RNA subunit

00:48:21.437 --> 00:48:23.520
and the protein subunit in E. coli?

00:48:23.520 --> 00:48:25.380
- Just a minute, could you stand

00:48:25.380 --> 00:48:27.100
a little bit further
back from the microphone?

00:48:27.100 --> 00:48:28.940
Not that far back, okay.

00:48:28.940 --> 00:48:32.250
- [Audience Member] So much
we know about the biogenesis

00:48:32.250 --> 00:48:36.330
of the RNA and protein
subunits in E. coli?

00:48:36.330 --> 00:48:39.280
I mean specifically when the bacteria grow

00:48:39.280 --> 00:48:41.908
under different conditions
like under stress

00:48:41.908 --> 00:48:44.420
or under rich medium.

00:48:44.420 --> 00:48:46.811
Do we see any--
- For the protein?

00:48:46.811 --> 00:48:47.990
- [Audience Member] As
well as the RNA subunit.

00:48:47.990 --> 00:48:50.650
- Okay.
- Is there any regulation?

00:48:50.650 --> 00:48:52.850
- The protein is made in an operon

00:48:53.930 --> 00:48:56.153
with some ribosomal proteins in it.

00:48:58.570 --> 00:49:02.070
Supposedly there is a binding,

00:49:02.070 --> 00:49:05.932
the sequence of the
upstream part of that operon

00:49:05.932 --> 00:49:10.320
has a binding site for the RNA subunits.

00:49:10.320 --> 00:49:11.950
But we've done a number of experiments

00:49:11.950 --> 00:49:13.450
in which we tried to regulate

00:49:13.450 --> 00:49:16.630
the amount of RNA and
the protein in E. coli

00:49:16.630 --> 00:49:19.040
and none of them have worked.

00:49:19.040 --> 00:49:20.093
That is to say,

00:49:21.150 --> 00:49:22.490
changing the amount of RNA

00:49:22.490 --> 00:49:23.930
doesn't change the amount of protein.

00:49:23.930 --> 00:49:25.100
Changing the amount of protein

00:49:25.100 --> 00:49:26.570
doesn't change the amount of RNA.

00:49:26.570 --> 00:49:28.470
That's about all I can say about that.

00:49:29.920 --> 00:49:32.190
Is that what you wanted to know?

00:49:32.190 --> 00:49:33.090
- [Audience Member] Because I'm wondering

00:49:33.090 --> 00:49:35.270
whether the tRNA synthesis

00:49:35.270 --> 00:49:38.393
is affected by that?
- Oh, that's a separate issue.

00:49:40.290 --> 00:49:44.933
The RNA subunit is under
relaxed stringent control.

00:49:47.100 --> 00:49:50.750
And I think so is the protein subunit.

00:49:50.750 --> 00:49:54.110
So if you starve the cells for amino acids

00:49:54.110 --> 00:49:56.320
or they go into stationary phase,

00:49:56.320 --> 00:49:59.903
you stop making both the
RNA and the protein subunit.

00:49:59.903 --> 00:50:01.380
- [Audience Member] Interesting.

